\mathbb{C}
f(z) = \sum\limits_{n=0}^\infty \frac{z^{2n}(-1)^{n}}{(2n)!}
\epsilon > 0
\delta > 0
|z-w| < \delta \longrightarrow |f(z) - f(w)| < \epsilon
\forall z,w \in \mathbb{C}
cos(z)
f(z) = cos(z)
|cos(z) - cos(w)| < \epsilon \longrightarrow -\epsilon < cos(z) - cos(w) < \epsilon 
cos^{-1}
|z-w| < cos^{-1}(\epsilon)
\delta = cos^{-1}(\epsilon)
a_n:=\frac{z^{2n}(-1)^n}{(2n)!}\implies\;
\frac{a_{n+1}}{a_n}=\left|\frac{z^{2n+2}(-1)^{n+1}}{(2n+2)!}\cdot\frac{(2n)!}{z^{2n}(-1)^n}\right|=|z|^2\frac1{(2n+1)(2n+2)}\xrightarrow[n\to\infty]{}0
\;z\in\Bbb C\;
\cos z=\sum\limits_{n=0}^\infty \frac{z^{2n}(-1)^{n}}{(2n)!}
